{
    "identity": "nprot-175",
    "title": "RNA isolation",
    "content": [
        {
            "header": "Introduction",
            "content": "This protocol was used in the above _Nature Immunology_ paper"
        },
        {
            "header": "Reagents",
            "content": "Trizol \\(GibcoRL, 10296)\r\n\n\n100% Isopropanol \\(Fisher Scientific, A416-500)\r\n\n\n70% Ethanol \\(Sigma E702-3)\r\n\n\nDepC Treated water \\(Ambion 9920)\r\n\n\nChloroform \\(Fisher Scientific C298-500)"
        },
        {
            "header": "Procedure",
            "content": "1) Pellet cells and resuspend in 1 mL of Trizol \\(I have difficulty isolating quality RNA from less than 1 X 10\n6\nprimary T cells). 1 mL of Trizol can be used for 1 X 10\n6\nto 10 X 10\n6\n.  It is best to brush the pelleted cells along a rack to dislodge them from the bottom of the tube. Sometimes aggregates will still be visible. Do not resuspend.\r\n\n\n2) Incubate at room temperature for 5 minutes\r\n\n\n3) Add 200\u03bcL of Chloroform using a barrier pipette tip and shake each sample vigourously\r\n\n\n4) Incubate at room temperature for 3 minutes\r\n\n\n5) Centrifuge at 12000g for 15 minutes at 4\u00b0C\r\n\n\n6) Transfer upper aqueous phase into a new RNAase free tube \\(approximately 0.8-1 mL of volume)\r\n\n\n7) Add 0.5 mL of isopropanol/mL of Trizol used and shake vigourously \r\n\n\n8) Incubate at room temperature for 10 minutes\r\n\n\n9) Centrifuge at 12000g for 15 minutes at 4\u00b0C\r\n\n\n10) Pour off supernantant and wash pellet in with 1 mL of 75% ethanol \\( do not resuspend pellet rather squirt in ethanol so the pellet becomes dislodged from the bottom of tube)\r\n\n\n11)  Centrifuge at 12000g for 5 minutes at room temperature\r\n\n\n12) Pour off supernantant and briefly dry pellet \\(can use a 10\u03bcL pipette or a kimwipe corner to get rid of residual ethanol)\r\n\n\n13) Dissolve pellet in 30\u03bcL of DepC treated water and place at 55\u00b0C for 5-10 minutes.\r\n\n\n14) Spec and take 2\u03bcg for cDNA conversion. Store the rest of the RNA at -80\u00b0C."
        }
